main.name: Ayda Negash
main.description: I am a junior full-stack developer
main.bioQuote: The greatest glory in living lies not in never falling, but in rising every time we fall.
main.bio: This quote encapsulates my experience with coding. Through many trials and tribulations, I graduated from SMU's Full Stack Web Development Program.  I have come to love coding and all the ups and downs it entails. The mindset of expecting and accepting failure not only helped me in my coding journey, but in all aspects of life.  I happily welcome the life-long path of being a student and always learning and improving. Prior to the SMU program, I was an instructor at a Wallas Foundation Funded research site teaching Environmental Science and Art . In my spare time, I practice Brazilian Jiu Jitsu and  gardening. In the coming future I hope to become a Master black-belt coding gardener.
